  <prompt>
    Replace the hardcoded `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()` call site in
    `SprkChatAgentFactory.CreateAgentAsync` with a call to
    `IScopeResolverService.ResolvePersonaForChatAsync(tenantId, playbookId?)` (added in
    task 003). The resolver returns the most-specific-wins persona; the factory uses its
    `systemPrompt` field in the system-prompt assembly. With the SYS-DEFAULT row seeded
    (task 004), behavior MUST be identical to today for tenants with no override (FR-04
    binding).

    Critical-path context: this task is the Pillar 1 cutover. After it lands, tenant admins
    can change the chat-agent voice by creating a CUST- persona row in Power Apps â€” no
    code deploy required. NFR-01 conversational primacy binding: the resolver augments the
    system prompt but the agent ALWAYS retains conversational ability regardless of which
    persona is resolved. Persona is the voice; conversation flow is intrinsic.

    Per project CLAUDE.md "MUST NOT hardcode persona text in C# after Pillar 1 lands" â€”
    `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()` MUST be either deleted OR retained ONLY as a dev-time
    fallback that asserts the resolver returned non-null (with a CRITICAL log + bug report).
    Decide which path during implementation; document in task notes.

    Regression test required: side-by-side comparison of CreateAgentAsync output before
    and after the cutover, with no overrides in place, MUST produce byte-identical system
    prompts.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with deep familiarity with `SprkChatAgentFactory.CreateAgentAsync`,
    the chat-agent system prompt assembly, NFR-01 conversational primacy contract, and the
    `IScopeResolverService` resolver pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SprkChatAgentFactory.CreateAgentAsync` invokes `ResolvePersonaForChatAsync` and uses
    the returned `systemPrompt`. With no tenant or playbook override in place, the
    assembled system prompt is byte-identical to pre-cutover output. A regression test
    asserts the equality. Build green; publish-size delta reported; ADR + NFR compliance
    verified.
  </goal>

