    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Cutover">
      Inject `IScopeResolverService` (constructor; module DI already registered). In `CreateAgentAsync`, replace `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()` call with the resolver call. Decide on `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()` fate: delete OR retain as null-safety assertion (CRITICAL log if resolver returns null + return the legacy text once as emergency fallback). Document the choice in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Add Regression Test">
      Add unit test asserting: with no tenant CUST- and no playbook persona, `CreateAgentAsync` produces a system prompt byte-identical to the captured baseline from Step 2. This is the FR-04 binding contract.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Add Conversational-Primacy Test">
      Add test asserting: even when a CUST- persona is resolved (mock), the agent retains the conversational layer (safety pipeline middleware chain still applied; chat history still consumed; no tool gate suppresses conversation). NFR-01 binding.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Build + Verify Publish Size">
      `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` â†’ 0 errors. `dotnet publish -c Release` â†’ measure delta vs baseline; report â‰¤+5 MB R6 budget.
